Panasonic to Start New Plant in China’s Suzhou Next Year

-- B y   T a k a s h i   A m a n o   a n d   M a r i k o   Y a s u
-- 
2011-10-07T06:08:24Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-07/panasonic-to-start-new-plant-in-china-s-suzhou-next-year.html
Panasonic Corp. (6752)  will start a new
factory in  China  to make systems used to fit electronic
components in personal computers and mobile phones, the company
said in a statement today.  The plant in Suzhou, eastern China, will be operated by
Panasonic’s factory solutions unit from April next year, the
company said in the statement, without providing an investment
amount. Osaka, Japan-based Panasonic, which currently uses
leased facilities in the Chinese city to make the products,
plans to boost the number of employees there to 650 from 360, it
said.  To contact the reporters on this story:
